1.8
log
@Let ircII install as ircII to avoid conflict with the irc package.
This is the *only simple way* to prevent users from running into trouble
if they decide to install both packages, which they are perfectly
entitled to do.
@
text
@d1 1
a1 1
# $OpenBSD: Makefile,v 1.7 2000/04/21 20:03:39 brad Exp $
d4 1
a4 1
DISTNAME=	ircii-4.4S
d18 1
d21 1
a21 1
CONFIGURE_ARGS=	--enable-ipv6 --exec-prefix=${PREFIX}
d28 1
a28 1
	cd ${PREFIX}/bin && rm -f ircII && ln -s ircII-4.4S ircII
@


